title: [Solhaven, Grebe and Eider]
description: Pushing his handcart, a journeyman butcher trundles wearily westward over the timbers of Grebe Lane.  Along both streets, many windows stand open to the cool night breeze.

Standing at the intersection, a journyeman butcher hawks his wares to the open windows of the dwellings that line the two streets.  More than one white-capped head or aproned torso can be seen in an attentive pose, harkening to his call.
